      "url": "about:srcdoc",
      "title": "NATA 2026 Complete Guide | EduAakashaA",
      "bodyText": "EduAakashaA\nProcess\nSchedule\nRankings\nCompare\nInterest Test\nInsights\nCOMPLETE GUIDE 2026\nMaster the NATA Exam\nShape Your Architecture Future\n\nYour definitive resource for NATA 2026 — exam process, schedule, top college rankings, career comparison, and personalized interest assessment.\n\n450+\nCOLLEGES\n200\nTOTAL MARKS\n3\nATTEMPTS\n5 Yrs\nB.ARCH\nSTEP BY STEP\nNATA 2026 Exam Process\n\nThe National Aptitude Test in Architecture (NATA) is conducted by the Council of Architecture (CoA).\n\n1\nOnline Registration\n\nRegister at nata.in with email and mobile. Upload photo & signature in JPEG. Pay fees online (General: ₹1750, SC/ST: ₹1250).\n\n2\nEligibility Check\n\n10+2 with Physics & Maths (50% aggregate) or 10+3 Diploma with Mathematics. Min age: 17 by July 31, 2026. No upper age limit.\n\n3\nExam Pattern\n\n3-hour exam, 200 marks. Part A: Drawing & Composition (offline, 80 marks). Part B: MCQ/NCQ (online, 120 marks). No negative marking.\n\n4\nAttempt & Score\n\nUp to 3 attempts in Phase 1. Best score is considered. Qualifying cutoff ~60/200. Top colleges need 120-145+. Results within 7-10 days.\n\n5\nAdmit Card\n\nDownload from nata.in. Available Tuesday for Friday exams, Wednesday for Saturday exams. Carry printed copy + valid photo ID.\n\n6\nCounselling & Admission\n\nColleges conduct their own counselling. Apply to 450+ CoA-recognized institutes across India. Meet individual college eligibility.\n\nEduAakashaA\nYour trusted guide for education & career counselling\nwww.eduaakashaa.in\nNATA by Council of Architecture (CoA). NIRF Rankings by Ministry of Education. All data from official sources.",
